08/09/2003
MONTREAL, Canada -- Goran Markovic's film "The Cordon" won the top prize at the prestigious international film festival in Montreal on Sunday (7 September). The movie examines the actions of the Serbian police during the anti-Milosevic demonstrations in 1997. Another film from Serbia-Montenegro, Dusan Kovacevic's "The Professional", netted the International Federation of Film Critics Prize and the Best Screenplay award. (Reuters - 08/09/03)
